# First, install `randr`
# Then, run `randr` to see which outputs do you have connected (example output below, there i have outputs `DP-2` and `HDMI-1` connected)
# Then create a file `$HOME/.xprofile` and add (this will make DP-2 primary monitor and will place if to the right of HDMI-1 monitor):

```sh
xrandr --output DP-2 --auto --right-of HDMI-1
```

